In C/C++ ['const] is not deep but shallow:

 std::shared_ptr<Foo> const foo = std::make_shared<Foo>(args); // Const foo
 ...
 foo->modify(); // Modifying foo's undelying data.

With Pimpl being a proxy it preserves the constness:

 Book const book = ...
 ...
 book

